description: Jeremy Corbyn has paid tribute to the victims of a terror attack in Manchester.
title: Jeremy Corbyn pays tribute to victims of Manchester terror attack

author: Mikey Smith
description: Jeremy Corbyn has closed the gap with Theresa May in the first poll conducted since the Manchester Bombing
title: Tory poll lead slashed to 5 points as Jeremy Corbyn gains ground on Theresa May

description: Jeremy Corbyn has linked Britain's involvement in military action abroad to terrorist attacks such as the Manchester suicide bomb as General Election campaigning resumed.
title: General Election 2017: Labour cut Tory poll lead to five points as Jeremy Corbyn criticised over speech on Manchester

description: The son of Jeremy Corbyn’s top election strategist said the Manchester suicide bombing had come at an “unbelievably ideal time” for Theresa May, according to reports.
title: Son of top Jeremy Corbyn aide claims Manchester terror attack came at 'ideal time' for Theresa May

author: Rob Merrick
description: Jeremy Corbyn is to take the hugely controversial step of blaming Britain’s foreign wars for terror attacks such as the Manchester suicide bombing. The Labour leader will claim a link between “wars our government has supported or fought in other countries and terrorism here at home”, as he relaunches his party’s election campaign on Friday after the three-day pause.
title: Jeremy Corbyn to blame UK foreign policy for terror attacks such as Manchester bombing

author: Tom Peck
description: Jeremy Corbyn has said he will "do whatever it takes" in the face of terrorism, in response to widespread criticism of his speech in which he sought to link the atrocity in Manchester with British foreign policy abroad. In fresh remarks, absent from the speech that was briefed to journalists on Thursday night, the Labour leader said: “Do not doubt my determination to take whatever action is necessary to keep our country safe and to protect our people on our streets, in our towns and cities, at our borders.”
title: Jeremy Corbyn says he will do 'whatever it takes' to defeat terrorism

author: Lizzie Dearden
description: Britain’s security minister has attacked Jeremy Corbyn for helping “justify” terrorism with a speech linking attacks with the UK’s foreign policy. Ben Wallace said the timing for the Labour leader’s speech days after the Manchester attack was “incredibly disappointing and crass”.
title: Security minister accuses Jeremy Corbyn of 'justifying' terrorism by linking foreign policy to attacks

author: Harley Tamplin for Metro.co.uk
description: Theresa May and Jeremy Corbyn have agreed to stop campaigning.
title: Party leaders' election campaigns suspended again after Manchester terror attack

author: By Steve Doughty Social Affairs Correspondent For The Daily Mail
description: The findings are a blow to the dream of Jeremy Corbyn and John McDonnell that a ‘basic income’ system would leave no family at risk of penury and hunger.
title: Corbyn’s radical benefits plan would 'worsen poverty'

author: By Stephanie Linning
description: Labour activist Tina Buckley, who was wearing a Jeremy Corbyn back pack, branded Theresa May 'the biggest terrorist' and the Government 'vile' in a rant outside the gates of Downing Street.
title: Woman HECKLES police and soldiers at Downing Street
